ivation of RNase L and restriction of infection. Our findings indicate that OAS proteins serve as pattern recognition receptors (PRRs) to recognize viral dsRNA and that this pathway is a primary response to virus rather than a secondary effect of interferon signaling.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Li, Yize", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dong, Beihua", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wei, Zuzhang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Silverman, Robert H.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Weiss, Susan R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Patton, John T.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/feb9010ae0c1e519e6b1fb4a12a83c40", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/e4091c1e9102cc15404039f59e0b63943201d1b4c24dd02b65507dd9f70a89af", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/BFT46XTQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/BFT46XTQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/87df3c56b8fa7aa704a3326b4f9043bf!/b69157-71609", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "6", "pages": "e02414-19", "title": "mBio", "volume": "10"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/feb9010ae0c1e519e6b1fb4a12a83c40"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435